{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_8","type":"mcp_tool_call","server":"codex_apps","tool":"github_fetch_file","arguments":{"repository_full_name":"BlueRay2/history-production","ref":"feature/xian","path":"xian/docs/VIDEO_CREATIVE_BRIEF.md","encoding":"utf-8"},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"content\": \"# Video Creative Brief \\u2014 Xi'an\\n\\n**Phase:** 1 (consolidation) \\u00b7 **Author:** Claude \\u00b7 **Date:** 2026-04-22.\\n\\n## One-line premise\\n\\nXi'an (\\u897f\\u5b89) is the single city on Earth that has been the accidental centre of three world-scale histories: the First Emperor's eternal army (210 BCE, discovered 1974), the most cosmopolitan capital of the medieval world (Tang Chang'an, ~750 CE, 1 million people, 5 religions), and the kidnapping that forced China into its alliance against imperial Japan (December 1936) \\u2014 altering the course of WWII.\\n\\n## Working title (for Phase 6 SEO)\\n\\n**Xi'an: The City That Was the Centre of History Three Times**\\n(alternates: *\\\"Three Buried Capitals\\\"* / *\\\"The Farmer Who Found an Empire\\\"*)\\n\\n## Format spec\\n\\n| Spec | Value |\\n|---|---|\\n| Length | 7\\u201310 min (target ~8:30) |\\n| Narration | ~1,050\\u20131,150 words @ 135-150 wpm |\\n| Structure | 3-act |\\n| Cold open | 0:00\\u20130:15 Terracotta Army hook |\\n| First CTA | 0:55 |\\n| CTAs total | 4, inline, ~45 sec total time budget |\\n| Pattern interrupts | Every 45-60s |\\n| Language | English narration, English burn-in subs for Chinese names |\\n\\n## 3-act arc (from RETENTION_ARCH.md)\\n\\n1. **Act I \\u2014 The Buried Emperor** (0:00\\u20133:00) \\u2014 Terracotta Army discovery, Qin Shi Huang, mercury-sealed tomb\\n2. **Act II \\u2014 The Open City** (3:00\\u20136:00) \\u2014 Han \\u2192 Tang Chang'an, Silk Road, Nestorian/Muslim/Buddhist/Zoroastrian/Taoist pluralism\\n3. **Act III \\u2014 The Kidnapping** (6:00\\u20138:30) \\u2014 Ming walls (grace note), Xi'an Incident 1936, modern Xi'an closing\\n\\n## Cold open (locked)\\n\\n> *\\\"In 1974, a farmer digging a well in northwest China struck something hard. He'd just found the private army of China's first emperor \\u2014 eight thousand life-size clay soldiers, each with a different face, entombed for two thousand two hundred years. Two kilometres away lies his mausoleum, still sealed, because the soil there runs with mercury. This is the story of Xi'an \\u2014 the city where the First Emperor still keeps his court. And that's only the first of three global turning points that happened here.\\\"*\\n\\n## Open loops\\n\\n- **OL-1** planted 0:15 / paid 2:30: sealed tomb + mercury\\n- **OL-2** planted 3:00 / paid 3:30: \\\"different city rose on same valley\\\" \\u2192 Silk Road\\n- **OL-3** planted 4:30 / paid 5:30: \\\"five religions in working worship\\\" \\u2192 Nestorian stele\\n- **OL-4** planted 6:00 / paid 7:15: \\\"fate of WWII decided here\\\" \\u2192 Xi'an Incident\\n\\n## CTAs\\n\\n| # | Time | Type | One-line intent |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| CTA-1 | 0:55 | Subscribe + value restatement | Lock viewer for full journey |\\n| CTA-2 | 4:00 | Engagement question | \\\"Drop your city in comments\\\" |\\n| CTA-3 | 6:30 | Like + stay-with-me | Signal Act III intensity |\\n| CTA-4 | 8:00 | Reflection + next video | Close arc + channel retention |\\n\\nFull wording in `docs/plans/RETENTION_ARCH.md` \\u00a7 CTA placements.\\n\\n## Audience\\n\\n- **Primary:** Curious Lay Historian \\u2014 Anglo adult, 28-55, hook on \\\"specific facts + hidden continuity + science corrects myth\\\".\\n- **Secondary:** China-Curious Traveller \\u2014 aesthetic/food/walkability pull, 10-15% screen time.\\n- **Tertiary:** History-of-Ideas Reader \\u2014 one dedicated 60-90s beat on Tang cosmopolitanism, named historian citation.\\n\\nFull persona spec: `docs/audience/AUDIENCE_PERSONA.md`.\\n\\n## Anti-clickbait register\\n\\n- No \\\"MYSTERY\\\", \\\"SECRET\\\", \\\"INSANE\\\", \\\"YOU WON'T BELIEVE\\\".\\n- Named sources inline (Sima Qian Shiji, Portal 2007, Scientific Reports 2019 chrome paper, Whitfield Silk Road histories).\\n- Pop-culture pokes happen ONCE (chrome-myth beat ~2:45 acknowledges *The Mummy: Tomb of the Dragon Emperor* by name, then corrects the record in 15 seconds).\\n\\n## Primary reveal (structural payoff)\\n\\n**Tang Chang'an was the world's largest city, ~1 million people, 5 religions in working worship, when contemporary London was ~10,000.** This reframes how the viewer thinks about medieval world centers. Positioned as Act II climax.\\n\\n## Visual/music intent\\n\\n- CGI for Chang'an grid + Daming Palace; period-recreations for Yang Zhifa (well discovery), Sima Qian (writing Shiji), Chiang (pre-dawn kidnapping); modern drone + stock for transitions.\\n- Traditional Chinese instruments (erhu, guqin, pipa) blended with cinematic orchestral bed. NO synth/electronic.\\n- Palette progression Act I warm-earth \\u2192 Act II saturated Tang \\u2192 Act III sepia 1936 \\u2192 modern.\\n\\nFull mood map: RETENTION_ARCH.md \\u00a7 Mood map.\\n\\n## Key facts that MUST appear (phase 2 SCRIPT compliance checklist)\\n\\n- 1974 / Yang Zhifa / Lintong / farmer digging a well\\n- 700,000 workers (Sima Qian Shiji)\\n- ~8,000 figures (current estimate post-excavation)\\n- Originally painted, colors oxidised minutes after air exposure\\n- Chrome-plating is a MYTH \\u2014 2019 Scientific Reports paper; preservation is bronze alloy + soil chemistry\\n- Mercury soil readings 100\\u00d7 background confirm Shiji's mercury-rivers account\\n- Mausoleum unexcavated \\u2014 modern preservation choice, not ancient curse\\n- Tang Chang'an population ~1M, grid plan\\n- Western Market \\u2014 Sogdians, Persians, Arabs, Turks, Indians, Japanese, Koreans\\n- Nestorian stele 781 CE, Syriac inscription, Alopen arrived 635 CE\\n- Great Mosque founded 742 CE, Chinese-temple form with Mecca alignment\\n- Daming Palace 4.5\\u00d7 Forbidden City\\n- 1936 Xi'an Incident \\u2014 Chiang Kai-shek kidnapped at Huaqing Pool, Second United Front result\\n- Wu Zetian ruled from Xi'an (only female emperor of China) \\u2014 optional grace note\\n\\n## Key facts that MUST NOT appear\\n\\n- Any claim of \\\"ancient chrome-plating technology\\\" EXCEPT to debunk it (scientific consensus 2019).\\n- Any claim that the central tomb contains \\\"treasures\\\" or \\\"mysteries\\\" beyond what Sima Qian documented \\u2014 we lead with the documented account + modern mercury evidence, avoid speculation.\\n- Any \\\"ancient aliens\\\" / \\\"lost technology\\\" / \\\"curse\\\" framing, even ironically.\\n\\n## Deliverables for next phases\\n\\n- **Phase 2** (Codex): SCRIPT.md ~1,050 words, 3 acts, 4 CTAs, 4 open loops, inline visual-motif anchors.\\n- **Phase 3** (Codex): TELEPROMPTER.md \\u2014 SCRIPT broken into ElevenLabs v3 tags + reader-friendly cadence marks.\\n- **Phase 4** (Codex): ALL_CLIPS.md \\u2014 40-60 hero prompt variants for Sora/Kling/Flow/Seedance (by persona fit).\\n- **Phase 5** (Codex): COST_ESTIMATE.md.\\n- **Phase 6** (Codex): SEO_PACKAGE.md \\u2014 5 title variants, canonical + 2 alt descriptions, 15 tags, thumbnail concepts with \\\"Hope In Ashes\\\" style discipline.\\n- **Phase 7** (Codex): MUSIC_CUES.md + CTA_PLACEMENT.md.\\n- **Phase 8**: parallel Codex + Gemini proofreading per `docs/tz/dashboard-kpi/process.md` review workflow.\\n\\n## Status\\n\\nPhase 1 \\u2705 complete. Phase 2 ready for Codex delegation.\\n\", \"encoding\": \"utf-8\", \"sha\": \"0d9449590838cc598a7c54957197f79d9bf2fb22\", \"display_url\": \"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/blob/feature/xian/xian/docs/VIDEO_CREATIVE_BRIEF.md\", \"display_title\": \"VIDEO_CREATIVE_BRIEF.md\"}"}],"structured_content":null},"error":null,"status":"completed"}}
